- `P[stoppedValue X τ|hσ.measurableSpace]`: This is $\mathbb{E}[X_\tau \mid \mathcal{F}_\sigma]$.

The problem is a direct application of the submartingale property. In a submartingale, the value at a stopping time is less than or equal to the value at a later time. Since $\tau \wedge \sigma \leq \tau$, we have $X_{\tau \wedge \sigma} \leq X_\tau$.

